cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.DC 

The paper deals with the performance analysis and optimization of a mobile edge caching system with full-duplex transmission, which involves aspects of networking (cs.NI), information theory (cs.IT), multimedia (cs.MM), control systems (cs.SY), and distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper discusses the delivery time performance of the system, which is a key metric in networking and multimedia applications. The optimization framework proposed in the paper involves linear and optimal precoding designs, which are related to information theory. The paper also discusses the cooperation among the edge nodes, which is related to control systems and distributed computing. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, and cs.DC, in that order.
